com.xiantrimble.combinatorics
Interface Combinatoric<T>

Type Parameters:
T - the type of the elements being combined or permuted.
All Superinterfaces:
java.util.Collection<T[]>, java.lang.Iterable<T[]>, java.util.List<T[]>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractCombinatoric, Combinations, IndexBasedPermutations, Permutations
public interface Combinatoric<T>
extends java.util.List<T[]>

The root interface for combinations and permutations. The individual elements of the combinations and permutations are returned as arrays.

Author:
Christian Trimble
